{
  "texts": [
    "For example, a study found that a model performed better on the Facebook codebase than on Instagram, likely because the former had ten times more training examples available [8].",
    "Similarly, models pre-trained on general-purpose GitHub repositories may fail to generate effective tests for specialized domains, such as High-Performance Computing [76] or complex C++ projects [17], unless specialized fine-tuning is applied.",
    "Evaluation Rigor and Gaps in Practice.Beyond the technical obstacles inherent to the models themselves, a third category of challenges arises from the surrounding ecosystem.",
    "This includes the scientific methodology used to measure progress and the practical hurdles of industrial deployment.",
    "These challenges concern the tools and processes used to gauge success, as well as the economic and logistical barriers that hinder the translation of promising research into widespread industrial practice.In industry, a prominent challenge is the rapid and continuous evolution of LLM technology itself, which renders any one-off technical evaluation potentially obsolete within months."
  ]
}